---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Net Worth at 30: What Is Good in 2024? (Federal Reserve Data)";
const description = "What is a good net worth at 30? See median net worth for Americans under 35 using Federal Reserve SCF data. Find out if you are ahead, behind, or right on track.";

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is $100,000 a good net worth at 30?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, $100,000 is an excellent net worth at 30. The median net worth for Americans under 35 is only $39,000. Having $100k puts you well into the top 50% and on track to hit the top 25% (which is $145,000) before you turn 35."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What should net worth be at 30?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "There is no single rule, but a common benchmark (like Fidelity's) suggests having 1x your annual salary saved by age 30. If you earn $60,000, aiming for a $60,000 net worth is a solid target. The actual median in the US is $39,000."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How does student debt affect net worth at 30?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Student debt is the biggest reason many 30-year-olds have a negative net worth. Because net worth is assets minus liabilities, a $50,000 student loan balance requires $50,000 in assets just to reach a net worth of $0."
      }
    }
  ]
};
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} slot="head" />

  <main class="px-4 py-12 max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-12">
    <!-- Hero Header -->
    <header class="text-center space-y-4">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-900 dark:text-white leading-tight">
        Net Worth at 30: What Is Good, <span class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400">Average, and Exceptional?</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-400 text-base md:text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        Turning 30 is a major financial milestone. Find out exactly where you stand compared to your peers using the latest 2022 Federal Reserve Survey of Consumer Finances (SCF) data for Americans under 35.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Key Stat Box -->
    <div class="bg-emerald-700 rounded-2xl p-6 md:p-8 text-white text-center shadow-xl space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-emerald-100">The Official Benchmark</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 divide-y md:divide-y-0 md:divide-x divide-emerald-500/50">
        <div class="pt-4 md:pt-0">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-emerald-200 mb-1">Median Net Worth (Under 35)</p>
          <p class="text-4xl font-black">$39,000</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-emerald-100 mt-2">The exact middle point. 50% have more, 50% have less.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pt-4 md:pt-0">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-emerald-200 mb-1">Average Net Worth (Under 35)</p>
          <p class="text-4xl font-black">$183,500</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-emerald-100 mt-2">Heavily skewed upwards by multi-millionaires in their early 30s.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Milestones Grid -->
    <section class="space-y-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Net Worth Milestones at Age 30</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-400">Here is the full breakdown of net worth percentiles for the "Under 35" age bracket:</p>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-l-red-500 bg-white/95 dark:bg-slate-900/40 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 shadow-sm">
          <p class="text-xs font-bold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-widest">Below Median</p>
          <p class="text-2xl font-black text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-1">Under $39k</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mt-2">Bottom 50%. Often dealing with student loans or just starting to save.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-l-blue-500 bg-white/95 dark:bg-slate-900/40 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 shadow-sm">
          <p class="text-xs font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-widest">Median</p>
          <p class="text-2xl font-black text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-1">$39,000</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mt-2">The exact 50th percentile. You are right in the middle.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-l-emerald-500 bg-white/95 dark:bg-slate-900/40 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 shadow-sm">
          <p class="text-xs font-bold text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 uppercase tracking-widest">Top 25%</p>
          <p class="text-2xl font-black text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-1">$145,000+</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mt-2">75th percentile. Strong savings, likely maxing out 401(k) or owning a home.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-l-violet-500 bg-white/95 dark:bg-slate-900/40 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 shadow-sm">
          <p class="text-xs font-bold text-violet-600 dark:text-violet-400 uppercase tracking-widest">Top 10%</p>
          <p class="text-2xl font-black text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-1">$340,000+</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mt-2">90th percentile. Exceptional wealth for this age, often from high income or equity.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Content Sections -->
    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Why Net Worth at 30 Varies So Wildly</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
        If you feel behind at 30, remember that the late 20s and early 30s are highly volatile. Some people have been working for 8 years and have built significant 401(k) balances. Others just finished medical school or a PhD and are starting at a massive negative net worth due to student loans. Buying a house can also drastically shift numbers depending on how home equity is calculated.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">What Are the Biggest Net Worth Killers in Your 30s?</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-3 list-disc pl-5 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-400">
        <li><strong class="text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Student Debt:</strong> Carrying high-interest student loans limits your ability to invest and compound wealth early.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Lifestyle Inflation:</strong> Increasing your spending immediately as your salary grows, leaving no margin for investing.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Not getting the 401(k) match:</strong> Leaving free employer money on the table is the #1 missed opportunity in your 20s and 30s.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">5 Ways to Dramatically Increase Your Net Worth Between 30 and 40</h2>
      <ol class="space-y-3 list-decimal pl-5 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-400">
        <li><strong>Automate Your Investments:</strong> Set up automatic transfers to a brokerage or IRA immediately after payday.</li>
        <li><strong>Max Out Tax-Advantaged Accounts:</strong> Use 401(k)s, IRAs, and HSAs to lower your tax burden and accelerate growth.</li>
        <li><strong>Focus on Income Growth:</strong> Your 30s are prime earning years. Negotiate salaries, upskill, or build side income.</li>
        <li><strong>Avoid High-Interest Debt:</strong> Keep credit card balances at zero. Pay down any debt over 6-7% interest aggressively.</li>
        <li><strong>Let Compounding Work:</strong> The money you invest at 30 has 35 years to grow before retirement. Stay invested.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA Box -->
    <div class="bg-emerald-700 rounded-2xl p-8 text-center shadow-xl space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Find Your Exact Percentile</h2>
      <p class="text-emerald-100 max-w-lg mx-auto">Stop guessing. Enter your specific age and net worth to see exactly where you rank among all Americans.</p>
      <a href="/" class="inline-block mt-4 px-6 py-3 bg-white text-emerald-700 font-bold rounded-xl hover:bg-emerald-50 transition-colors shadow-lg">
        Calculate Your Exact Percentile
      </a>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        {faqSchema.mainEntity.map(faq => (
          <details class="group bg-white/95 dark:bg-slate-900/40 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 rounded-xl p-5 cursor-pointer">
            <summary class="flex justify-between items-center font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white list-none">
              {faq.name}
              <span class="text-slate-500 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▼</span>
            </summary>
            <p class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-400 mt-3 leading-relaxed">
              {faq.acceptedAnswer.text}
            </p>
          </details>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="text-center text-xs text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-500 pt-8 border-t border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800">
      Data Source: Federal Reserve Survey of Consumer Finances (SCF), 2022.
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
